Vote - AcceptText - Accept text. Line 1: (Π(αρὰ)) -> (π(αρὰ)). Line 1: should it be mentionned that the papyrus has πρωτοκωμτμτ? Line 1: note that τῶν was forgotten in the SB, but is in the ed. pr. and on the papyrus (see the plate). Line 1: Λευ̣κο̣ὺ̣ -> Λευ̣κο̣ῦ̣. Line 1: note that Mitthof's correction on the ed.pr. is already incorporated in the SB, which prints Λευ̣κο̣ῦ̣ Π̣[ύργου. Line 1: >[ τῷ -> > [τῷ. Line 2: note that Mitthof's correction on the ed.pr. is incorporated in the SB, but with a mistake: καθαρ(ὼς) καὶ άκ̣ρ̣ό̣τ̣[ως. Line 3: is *x**x**x* correct for the three crosses? Line 3: the ### indicates that the text is in a box, but how is the "end" of the text in the box indicated? Line 3: SB made a mistake in Ἀνίκητ[ος], it prints Ἀνίκητος (without []): the ed. pr. has Ἀνίκετ[ος] (with an ε).
